introduction: This video discusses a virtual conference that will take place on February 15th and 22nd. The conference features an AI product owner track, an engineering track, and hands-on workshops. Some of the keynote speakers include Jason Louie, Shrea Shanar, Tunji, and Golden. The conference also focuses on AI ethics, particularly in terms of evaluating the responses and individual span levels of AI models. The video emphasizes the importance of getting stuff out as fast as possible and evaluating the outcomes.

sections.title: Section 1: Introduction to the Virtual Conference
content: The virtual conference is happening on February 15th and 22nd.
It features an AI product owner track, an engineering track, and hands-on workshops.
Keynote speakers include Jason Louie, Shrea Shanar, Tunji, and Golden.
The conference focuses on AI ethics, particularly in terms of evaluating AI responses.

sections.title: Section 2: AI Product Owner Track
content: The AI product owner track covers various topics related to AI product ownership.
Some of the topics include AI product strategy, AI product design, and AI product management.
The track also explores the intersection of AI and human-computer interaction.
Examples of AI product ownership case studies are presented.

sections.title: Section 3: Engineering Track
content: The engineering track focuses on the technical aspects of AI development.
Topics covered include AI algorithms, deep learning, and natural language processing.
The track also discusses the challenges and best practices in AI engineering.
Examples of AI engineering projects are presented.

sections.title: Section 4: Hands-on Workshops
content: The hands-on workshops provide attendees with hands-on experience in AI development.
Workshops cover topics such as AI model building, data preprocessing, and model evaluation.
Attendees can work on their own projects or collaborate with others during the workshops.
Examples of projects built during the workshops are presented.

sections.title: Section 5: AI Ethics and Evaluation
content: The conference also focuses on AI ethics, particularly in terms of evaluating AI responses.
The importance of getting stuff out as fast as possible and evaluating the outcomes is emphasized.
Individual span level evaluations and evals customization are discussed.
Examples of AI models and their evaluation methods are presented.
